LARDD 1
TITLE LardOS Driver Branch
TEXT User-installable driver catalog for LardOS.
SECTION Formats
ITEM DRFL 2 is the native driver-file format. It carries editable CODE lines inside the .drfl file.
ITEM RXR bundles a DRFL driver file with a small RXE helper app so users can install drivers with rxr install.
ITEM LARDD documents drivers in a LardOS-native readable form.
SECTION Folders
ITEM network -> network adapters.
ITEM storage -> disk and controller driver files.
ITEM display -> display and framebuffer driver files.
ITEM input -> keyboard, mouse, and pointer driver files.
ITEM usb -> USB controller and device driver files.
ITEM vm -> virtual-machine helper driver files.
ITEM bundles -> combined packs for common setups.
ITEM tools -> small in-tree helper tools.
SECTION Install
ITEM Put a wanted .rxr on A: or Z:.
ITEM rxr verify A:core-drivers.rxr
ITEM rxr install A:core-drivers.rxr
ITEM drivers reload
ITEM drivers
ITEM drivers show rtl8139
ITEM sync
ITEM Restart if the driver file must be present during early boot probing.
SECTION Honesty
ITEM DRFL is the driver source/control body, not only a hardware descriptor.
ITEM The code body stays visible through drivers show and remains user-editable.
END
